---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Space — Astronomy Terms That Score Big"
  description="Space and astronomy terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUASAR (15pts), NEBULA (8pts), GALAXY (14pts). Astronomy vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble space words, quasar scrabble points, nebula scrabble, galaxy scrabble word, astronomy vocabulary scrabble, space words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Space — Astronomy Terms That Score Big","description":"Space and astronomy terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUASAR (15pts), NEBULA (8pts), GALAXY (14pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-space"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUASAR a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! QUASAR scores 15 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, S=1, A=1, R=1). One of the strongest Q-with-U words using common supporting tiles. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play GALAXY in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. GALAXY scores 14 points (G=2, A=1, L=1, A=1, X=8, Y=4). The X=8 and Y=4 tiles provide 12 of the 14 points in this 6-letter word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is NEBULA valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! NEBULA scores 8 points (N=1, E=1, B=3, U=1, L=1, A=1). A useful 6-letter word for clearing common tiles when you need board coverage."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Space — Astronomy Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The cosmos offers Scrabble players a constellation of high-scoring words. QUASAR shines at 15 points with Q=10, GALAXY blazes at 14 points through X=8 and Y=4, and NEBULA provides solid board coverage. These celestial terms will launch your score into orbit.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUASAR (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GALAXY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZENITH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NEBULA</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Stellar Play</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUASAR — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, A=1, S=1, A=1, R=1 · 6 letters · Q=10 with natural QU start</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A quasi-stellar radio source emitting enormous energy. QUASAR scores 15 points from 6 tiles (2.5 pts/tile). It provides a reliable Q-dump word using only common supporting tiles (U, A, S, A, R). On a double-word square, that's 30 points.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Cosmic Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌌 GALAXY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · G=2, A=1, L=1, A=1, X=8, Y=4 · Star system</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ ZENITH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · Z=10, E=1, N=1, I=1, T=1, H=4 · Highest point</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌀 NEBULA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · N=1, E=1, B=3, U=1, L=1, A=1 · Gas cloud</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☄️ COMET</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · C=3, O=1, M=3, E=1, T=1 · Ice body orbiting sun</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Space Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ORBIT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PULSAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ASTRAL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COSMIC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LUNAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Space Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUASAR is a premium Q play:</span> Unlike QI (11pts in 2 tiles), QUASAR uses 6 tiles for 15 points with better board coverage. The double-A requirement is easily met since A is the most common tile.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GALAXY deploys X+Y together:</span> When holding both X=8 and Y=4, GALAXY converts them into 14 points. Supporting tiles (G, A, L, A) are all common — this combination is realistic to draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZENITH stacks Z+H:</span> Z=10 and H=4 combine for 14 of ZENITH's 18 total points. The remaining tiles (E, N, I, T) are among the most common in the bag.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Space words provide <span class="text-white font-medium">premium tile deployment options</span>. QUASAR handles Q, GALAXY pairs X+Y, and ZENITH combines Z+H. These words solve high-value tile placement when standard short words aren't available on the board.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid space word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
